thread.title_full: Young Iqbal Club derail Central Railway in NDFA Elite Division Football League - The Times of India

author: Suhas Nayse
title: Young Iqbal Club derail Central Railway in NDFA Elite Division Football League
text:
NAGPUR: A splendid double strike by foreign recruit Izic propelled Young Iqbal Club to a resounding 3-0 victory over DSA Central Railway in the Meghe NDFA Elite Division Football League match at the Police Line Takli ground here on Thursday.
Izic struck a goal each in either half to derail the railmen. Sohrab Akhtar opened the Kamptee side's account in the 27th minute, while Izic increased the margin in the 30th and 85th minutes.
Earlier, in another one-sided encounter, Shakti Sporting Club outclassed Nagpur Star 3-1 in the Senior Division League. Sai Sailo slammed a brace, while Pawan Masram added one more in the 72nd minute. Rishab Patel scored a consolation goal for Nagpur Star in the 46th minute.
RESULTS
Elite Division: Young Iqbal Club 3 (Sohrab Akhtar 27th min, Izic 30th min, 85th min) bt DSA Central Railway 0.
Senior Division: Shakti Sporting 3 (Sai Sailo 31st min, 54th min, Pawan Masram 72nd min) bt Nagpur Star 1 (Rishab Patel 46th min).
On Friday
Elite Division: Young Muslim FC vs City Police at SRPF ground, Hingna (3 pm).
Senior Division: Nagpur City 'B' vs Orange City Club at Police Line Takli ground (3 pm).
